                <h1>Robin Hood: The Hero Who Stole for the People</h1>
                <p>Robin Hood, the legendary English folk hero, is celebrated for his daring exploits of stealing from the rich to give to the poor. Residing in Sherwood Forest with his band of Merry Men, he symbolizes justice and resistance against tyranny. His story of bravery and loyalty continues to inspire countless adaptations in literature and film.</p>
